article.headline: Akron 70, Ball St. 52
article.story: AKRON, Ohio (AP) -- Dru Joyce scored 16 points, including a 3-pointer in a 12-0 first-half run, to lead Akron past Ball State 70-52 on Saturday. With the Zips (17-4, 8-1 Mid-American Conference) holding a 19-17 lead, Chris McNight and Romeo Travis each hit shots inside, Joyce and Nick Dials hit 3-pointers and Cedrick Middleton made a layup to push the lead to 31-17. The Zips stretched their winning streak to nine in a row overall and seven straight at home. Dials and Jeremiah Wood each added 12 points and Middleton had 11 for Akron, which shot 54 percent from the field. Peyton Stovall had 15 points and Skip Mills 10 for the Cardinals (7-15, 3-6). Akron's defense held Ball State scoreless for nearly six minutes in the opening half during the 12-0 run, forcing six turnovers and recording a pair of steals.
